text: Dmitry Vitalyevich Sarsembayev () (born 29 November 1997) is a Russian snowboarder. He competed in the 2017 FIS Snowboard World Championships, and in the 2018 Winter Olympics, in parallel giant slalom. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Russian male snowboarders Category:Olympic snowboarders of Russia Category:Snowboarders at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:People from Tashtagol Category:Universiade gold medalists for Russia Category:Universiade bronze medalists for Russia Category:Universiade medalists in snowboarding Category:Competitors at the 2019 Winter Universiade
